g.text: UML Diagram: Class Map in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.
a.xlink:title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.

a.title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).
a.xlink:title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).

a.title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.
a.xlink:title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.

a.title: ― CorrespondenceDefinition: Describes the commonalities and differences between two members using a textual description of both commonalities and differences plus an optional coding of the type of commonality.
a.xlink:title: ― CorrespondenceDefinition: Describes the commonalities and differences between two members using a textual description of both commonalities and differences plus an optional coding of the type of commonality.

a.title: ― InstanceVariableMap: Key value relationship for two or more logical records where the key is one or more equivalent instance variables and the value is a defined relationship or a relationship to a set value.
a.xlink:title: ― InstanceVariableMap: Key value relationship for two or more logical records where the key is one or more equivalent instance variables and the value is a defined relationship or a relationship to a set value.

a.title: ― ConceptMap: Correspondence between concepts in a correspondence table.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptMap: Correspondence between concepts in a correspondence table.
